entries.title: Peru extends state of emergency amid deadly protests
entries.description: Peru is seeing some of its worst violence in decades, which erupted last month following the ousting of former President Pedro Castillo, as protesters who oppose the current government call for political change in the country.

entries.title: Gen Z has a new 'vintage' technology to obsess over
entries.description: First, it was disposable cameras. Then it was low-rise jeans. Now, Gen-Z's latest "vintage" obsession is the flip phone -- that mid-1990s era phone that has suddenly become oh so popular with millennials.

entries.title: China allows Didi to resume signing up new users as tech crackdown eases
entries.description: Ride-hailing giant Didi received approval to resume new user registration in China, it said Monday, providing more evidence that Beijing's regulatory crackdown on tech giants might be coming to an end.

entries.title: American held in Iran launches hunger strike
entries.description: An American wrongfully detained in Iran is calling on President Joe Biden to take notice of US detainees there, launching a hunger strike Monday to mark seven years since he was left behind in a prisoner swap that brought other Americans home.
